      "writtenOn": "2026-05-27T03:52:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Two problems:\n\n1. Always shown: Because `version` is always truthy (defaults to 3), the expanded view always renders the version row even when the API omitted `Version`.\n2. Misleading default: Inventing `3` when the field is absent is incorrect for audit/compliance use cases this feature targets.\n\nAdditionally, Redfish/X.509 Version is the ASN.1 integer (e.g. 2 means X.509 v3), not a human-friendly “version 3”. Displaying the raw integer without translation may confuse admins.\n\nRecommendation: Only store/display Version when present. Consider displaying Version + 1 with a label like “X.509 v3”, or omit the field if semantics are unclear.",
      "revId": "806a55ec1fb8c51e284c45e8b81925e6a18c8ba6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
